👊Chapter 1: Introduction to Python Programming and Practical Projects

  ⚡This content provides a comprehensive introduction to Python programming, starting from the basics and advancing to practical applications including GUI development and API integration.
  ⚡Key concepts covered include variables, data types (strings, integers, floats, booleans), type casting, user input, control structures (if statements, loops), functions, error handling, object-oriented programming, file handling, multithreading, and GUI development using PyQt5.
  ⚡Vocabulary terms such as Python interpreter, IDE (Integrated Development Environment), API (Application Programming Interface), string methods, list comprehensions, decorators, exception handling, modules, classes, inheritance, polymorphism, duck typing, static and class methods, magic methods, property decorators, signals and slots in PyQt5, and layouts are introduced and explained.
